{"id": "EUVD-2018-2990", "enisaUuid": "39f9f25c-a0b2-3054-b181-b1762a79e260", "description": "A flaw was found in the Linux kernel present since v4.0-rc1 and through v4.13-rc4. A crafted network packet sent remotely by an attacker may force the kernel to enter an infinite loop in the cipso_v4_optptr() function in net/ipv4/cipso_ipv4.c leading to a denial-of-service. A certain non-default configuration of LSM (Linux Security Module) and NetLabel should be set up on a system before an attacker could leverage this flaw.", "datePublished": "2018-08-27T13:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T07:54:35", "baseScore": 5.9, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2018-10938.html", "https://www.debian.org/security/2018/dsa-4308", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2018-10938", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2018-10938.html", "http://seclists.org/oss-sec/2018/q3/179", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3797-2/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3797-1/", "https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/commit/?id=40413955ee265a5e42f710940ec78f5450d49149", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2018/10/msg00003.html", "http://www.securitytracker.com/id/1041569", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=CVE-2018-10938", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/105154"], "aliases": ["CVE-2018-10938"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 5.78, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "c1ff11b0-cd6e-3fa5-b45e-2ef2ea160293", "product": {"name": "n/a"}, "product_version": "n/a"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "22887c15-0c38-3e60-a3b7-9616398ddbfc", "vendor": {"name": "n/a"}}], "isExploited": false}